The ECM captured these sensor readings at the exact moment the fault triggered:

  DEF level:       {def_level_pct}%
  Engine RPM:      {engine_rpm}
  Engine hours:    {equipment_hours}
  Derate active:   {derate_active}
  Fault count:     {fault_count} times

DEF derate threshold: 10% triggers Level 1 derate.
At {def_level_pct}% the ECM {'has' if '{derate_active}' == 'Yes' else 'has not'} triggered a derate.

This fault combination has appeared on X15 engines before.

Historical cases matching your fault codes ({fault_codes_active}):
  Similar cases found:  {similar_cases_found}
  Resolution success rate: {success_rate_pct}%
  Most common resolution: {most_common_resolution}
  TSB reference: {tsb_references}

What the history tells you:
In {similar_cases_found} previous cases with these codes, the resolution was {most_common_resolution} with a {success_rate_pct}% success rate.

Combine this with what you observed in Steps 1-4.

Historical cases matching {fault_codes_active} on X15 engines:

  Similar cases:       {similar_cases_found}
  Success rate:        {success_rate_pct}%
  Common resolution:   {most_common_resolution}
  TSB reference:       {tsb_references}

Combine with your observations from Steps 1-4:
- If duty cycle issue identified: forced regen likely sufficient
- If exhaust leak found: repair leak before regen
- If pressure sensor suspected: sensor test before regen
- If soot load >95%: physical inspection before regen attempt

Historical cases matching {fault_codes_active} on X15 engines:

  Similar cases:       {similar_cases_found}
  Success rate:        {success_rate_pct}%
  Common resolution:   {most_common_resolution}
  TSB reference:       {tsb_references}

Combine with your observations:
- High hours + carbon deposits visible: valve cleaning likely needed
- Low/contaminated coolant + code 2789: coolant issue is root cause
- Overdue service + high idle: maintenance-driven failure
- Recent coolant work + code 2789: incorrect coolant type suspected

Historical cases matching {fault_codes_active} on X15 engines:

  Similar cases:       {similar_cases_found}
  Success rate:        {success_rate_pct}%
  Common resolution:   {most_common_resolution}
  TSB reference:       {tsb_references}

Pattern assessment:
- Overdue filters + low pressure: filter replacement is likely resolution
- Water indicator positive: water contamination, filter + fuel drain needed
- Recent fueling from field tank: contamination suspected
- No obvious supply issue: high-pressure pump assessment needed
